```class Solution {
    public int minPartitions(String n) {
        int maxDigit = 0;
        for (char c : n.toCharArray()) {
            maxDigit = Math.max(maxDigit, c - '0');
        }
        return maxDigit;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the input string once, finding the maximum digit. Since the problem statement guarantees that the input string represents a positive decimal integer, the maximum digit will be the minimum number of deci-binary numbers needed to sum up to the input number.

